{{Infobox journal | title = Polish Journal of Philosophy | cover = pjphilcover.gif | editor = Sebastian Tomasz Kolodziejczyk | discipline = [[Philosophy]] | formernames = | abbreviation = Pol. J. Philos. | publisher = Institute of Philosophy, Jagiellonian University | country = Poland | frequency = Biannual | history = 2007–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.pjp.edu.pl/index.htm | link1 = http://www.pdcnet.org/pjphil/toc | link1-name = Online access | JSTOR = | OCLC = 137334904 | LCCN = 2007-224050 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1897-1652 | eISSN = 2154-3747 }} The '''''Polish Journal of Philosophy''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes original articles, reviews, and other items to promote continuing philosophical scholarship in Poland. It is published in English. Notable contributors include Peter Baumann, Arkadiusz Chrudzimski, [[Susan Haack]], Dale Jacquette, Stephen Palmquist, Roberto Poli, Władysław Stróżewski, and [[Jan Woleński]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdcnet.org/pjphil/toc|title=Tables of content, all volumes|accessdate=12 February 2012|work=Polish Journal of Philosophy}}</ref> The scope of the journal includes both the phenomenological school of Roman Ingarden and the Lvov-Warsaw school of analytic philosophy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pjp.edu.pl/index.htm|title=Aims & Scope|accessdate=12 February 2012|work=Polish Journal of Philosophy}}</ref> The ''Polish Journal of Philosophy'' is edited and published at the Institute of Philosophy, [[Jagiellonian University]] in [[Kraków]], Poland. All issues are available online from the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]].
