====Dominican Republic====
{{Main|White Dominicans}}
The 1750 estimates show that there were 30,863 whites, out of a total population of 70,625, in the colony of Santo Domingo.<ref name=Haines>[https://books.google.com/books?id=BPdgiysIVcgC&pg=PA495&lpg=PA495&dq=17,572+whites;+5,037+22,274++44,883&source=bl&ots=rUCNxNf12c&sig=91h4Iz56R2iugYUEcNtT5EXHc20&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCUQ6AEwAWoVChMIucqitfOmyAIVRjkaCh2E_Ahu#v=onepage&q=17%2C572%20whites%3B%205%2C037%2022%2C274%20%2044%2C883&f=false A Population History of North America] By Michael R. Haines, Richard H. Steckel</ref> The census of 1920 was the first national enumeration. The second census, taken in 1935, covered race, religion, literacy, nationality, labor force, and urban–rural residence.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=OE3XAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA5&dq=population+history+of+dominican+republic&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCQQ6AEwAWoVChMIp6v9y_-myAIVSD0UCh0_6wM7#v=onepage&q=population%20history%20of%20dominican%20republic&f=false Dominican Republic, Summary of Biostatistics: Maps and Charts, Population ...]  By United States. Bureau of the Census</ref>

